article.headline: Lehigh 35, Bucknell 16
article.story: LEWISBURG, Pa. -- JB Clark threw for a season-high 327 yards and one touchdown and ran for another score to lead Lehigh to a 35-16 win over Bucknell on Saturday. Clark was 24-for-37 for the Mountain Hawks (2-5, 2-0 Patriot League) and threw a 5-yard scoring pass to Alex Wojdowski with 5 seconds left in the first half for a 21-7 lead. Jake Drwal caught nine passes for 124 yards as Lehigh's offense totaled a season-best 461 yards. Lehigh's other four touchdowns were running plays: Michael Colvin from 4 yards out, Clark and Zach Barket on 1-yard bursts and Jaren Walker on a 2-yard rush. Marcello Trigg was 14-for-26 for 216 yards with one touchdown for Bucknell (3-4, 1-1). Trigg connected with Shaun Pasternak on a 43-yard scoring play for the final margin. The Mountain Hawks have beaten the Bison 12 straight times, including six consecutive in Lewisburg.
